article.headline: North Texas 62, Denver 48
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Quincy Williams had game highs of 17 points and nine rebounds to lead North Texas over Denver 62-48 Thursday night. Ben Bell added 10 points for the Mean Green (15-9, 6-7 Sun Belt). Joe Jackson scored 13 points and was the lone player in double figures for the Pioneers (11-13, 7-6). Jackson's three rebounds tied for team high. The Mean Green used a 16-2 run midway through the first half to take a 33-18 halftime lead. Adam McCoy scored all seven of his points during the run with a dunk, 3-pointer and fast-break layup. North Texas led by as many as 23 points in the second half, including a 60-37 lead before Denver ended the game on an 11-2 run. North Texas scored 38 points in the paint to only 18 for Denver, and won the rebounding battle 33-16.
